{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:34:35.239Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain Rule"},{"type":"text","text":" is the fundamental calculus formula that computes the derivative of a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"composite function"},{"type":"text","text":" (a function inside another function, like \"Russian nesting dolls\"). It's the mathematical backbone of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"backpropagation"},{"type":"text","text":" in neural networks, enabling efficient gradient computation through dozens of stacked layers by breaking down complex derivatives into simple local pieces."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mathematical definition:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For a composite function "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"y = f(g(x))"},{"type":"text","text":", the chain rule states:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"dy/dx = f'(g(x)) · g'(x)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In words"},{"type":"text","text":": The derivative of the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"outer function"},{"type":"text","text":" (evaluated at the inner function) times the derivative of the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"inner function"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternative notation (more intuitive):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If y = f(u) and u = g(x), then:\ndy/dx = dy/du × du/dx"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Natural reading"},{"type":"text","text":": \"The rate of change of y with respect to x equals the rate of change of y with respect to u, times the rate of change of u with respect to x\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Visual analogy — Russian nesting dolls:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Function composition: y = f(g(x))\n\nThink of it like nested dolls:\n  Outer doll: f(u)\n  Inner doll: g(x)\n\nTo differentiate:\n1. Open outer doll → differentiate f(u) → get f'(u)\n2. Plug in inner function → f'(g(x))\n3. Open inner doll → differentiate g(x) → get g'(x)\n4. Multiply: f'(g(x)) × g'(x) [web:179]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Factory analogy:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Raw material → Machine A → Intermediate → Machine B → Final product\n\nChain rule: How does raw material change affect final product?\n= (effect of Machine A) × (effect of Machine B)\n= du/dx × dy/du [web:181]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The chain rule is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"absolutely essential for machine learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ML Component"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How chain rule applies"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backpropagation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Computes gradients through neural network layers = chain rule applied recursively"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Neural Network Training"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Each layer is a function composition; chain rule differentiates through all layers"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Loss Minimization"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain rule computes ∂Loss/∂weight for millions of parameters"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Deep Learning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Enables training networks with 100+ layers by decomposing derivatives"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real example"},{"type":"text","text":": In GPT training, the loss depends on the output, which depends on layer N, which depends on layer N-1,..., which depends on input. Chain rule computes ∂Loss/∂weight₁ by multiplying all these local derivatives."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits — Key advantages"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Handles compositions"},{"type":"text","text":": Differentiate functions you can't easily expand"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local computation"},{"type":"text","text":": Break complex derivative into simple pieces"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Efficient"},{"type":"text","text":": Avoids expanding enormous composite expressions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Layer-by-layer"},{"type":"text","text":": Enables backpropagation through neural networks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recursive"},{"type":"text","text":": Applies to any number of composed functions"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-offs — Downsides and limitations"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Trade-off"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Impact"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Numerical instability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain of multiplications can explode or vanish (gradient issues)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Order matters"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Must apply chain rule in correct order (outer → inner)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Many layers → many chain rule applications → harder to debug"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works — Step-by-step computation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single-variable chain rule:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 1"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"y = sin(x²)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Identify outer and inner functions\n  Outer: f(u) = sin(u)\n  Inner: u = g(x) = x²\n\nStep 2: Differentiate outer function\n  f'(u) = cos(u)\n  f'(g(x)) = cos(x²)\n\nStep 3: Differentiate inner function\n  g'(x) = 2x\n\nStep 4: Multiply (chain rule)\n  dy/dx = cos(x²) × 2x"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 2"},{"type":"text","text":": "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"italic"}],"text":"y = (3x + 2)⁵"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: Identify functions\n  Outer: f(u) = u⁵\n  Inner: u = g(x) = 3x + 2\n\nStep 2: Differentiate outer\n  f'(u) = 5u⁴\n  f'(g(x)) = 5(3x + 2)⁴  ← Keep inner function!\n\nStep 3: Differentiate inner\n  g'(x) = 3\n\nStep 4: Multiply\n  dy/dx = 5(3x + 2)⁴ × 3 = 15(3x + 2)⁴"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common mistake — Forgetting to plug back inner function:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"WRONG: dy/dx = 5u⁴ × 3 = 15u⁴  ← u is not defined!\nCORRECT: dy/dx = 5(3x + 2)⁴ × 3 = 15(3x + 2)⁴  ← Plug in u = 3x + 2"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-variable chain rule (for neural networks):"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Extended chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If y depends on u, which depends on v, which depends on x:\ndy/dx = dy/du × du/dv × dv/dx"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In neural network"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loss L = f(w₃, w₂, w₁) where:\n  w₃ depends on w₂\n  w₂ depends on w₁\n\n∂L/∂w₁ = ∂L/∂w₃ × ∂w₃/∂w₂ × ∂w₂/∂w₁"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Python implementations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Manual computation:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\n# Function: y = sin(x²)\ndef f(x):\n    return np.sin(x**2)\n\n# Derivative using chain rule: dy/dx = cos(x²) × 2x\ndef derivative_chain_rule(x):\n    return np.cos(x**2) * 2 * x\n\n# Numerical verification\nx = 1.0\nh = 1e-5\nnumerical = (f(x + h) - f(x)) / h\nanalytical = derivative_chain_rule(x)\n\nprint(f\"Numerical: {numerical}\")      # ≈ 0.909\nprint(f\"Analytical: {analytical}\")    # ≈ 0.909 ✓"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"PyTorch (autograd):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import torch\n\nx = torch.tensor([1.0], requires_grad=True)\ny = torch.sin(x**2)\n\n# Automatic chain rule application\ny.backward()\n\nprint(f\"Derivative: {x.grad}\")  # ≈ 0.909 (matches chain rule)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain Rule in Backpropagation — The neural network application"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Neural network as function composition:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input x → Layer 1 → a₁ → Layer 2 → a₂ → ... → Layer N → Output → Loss\n\nMathematically:\n  a₁ = f₁(x)\n  a₂ = f₂(a₁) = f₂(f₁(x))\n  a₃ = f₃(a₂) = f₃(f₂(f₁(x)))\n  ...\n  Loss = L(aₙ) = L(fₙ(fₙ₋₁(...f₁(x)...)))\n\nThis is a COMPOSITION of functions! [web:180]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Computing ∂Loss/∂weight via chain rule:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For weight w in layer 1:\n\nLoss depends on output aₙ\naₙ depends on aₙ₋₁\naₙ₋₁ depends on aₙ₋₂\n...\na₂ depends on a₁\na₁ depends on w\n\n∂Loss/∂w = ∂Loss/∂aₙ × ∂aₙ/∂aₙ₋₁ × ∂aₙ₋₁/∂aₙ₋₂ × ... × ∂a₂/∂a₁ × ∂a₁/∂w"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Each term is a \"local derivative\""},{"type":"text","text":" — easy to compute!"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step-by-step backpropagation example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\n# Simple 2-layer neural network\n# Input → Layer 1 (w₁) → Activation → Layer 2 (w₂) → Output → Loss\n\n# Parameters\nw1 = 0.5\nw2 = 1.0\n\n# Input and target\nx = 2.0\ny_true = 3.0\n\n# Forward pass\na1 = w1 * x                 # Layer 1 output\na2 = np.tanh(a1)            # Activation\noutput = w2 * a2            # Layer 2 output\nloss = (output - y_true)**2 # MSE loss\n\nprint(f\"Loss: {loss:.4f}\")  # ≈ 0.25\n\n# Backward pass (chain rule!)\n# Compute ∂Loss/∂w1\n\n# Step 1: ∂Loss/∂output = 2(output - y_true)\ndLoss_dOutput = 2 * (output - y_true)\n\n# Step 2: ∂output/∂w2 = a2\ndOutput_dW2 = a2\n\n# Step 3: ∂output/∂a2 = w2\ndOutput_da2 = w2\n\n# Step 4: ∂a2/∂a1 = 1 - tanh²(a1) (derivative of tanh)\nda2_da1 = 1 - np.tanh(a1)**2\n\n# Step 5: ∂a1/∂w1 = x\nda1_dW1 = x\n\n# CHAIN RULE: Multiply all local derivatives\ndLoss_dW1 = dLoss_dOutput * dOutput_da2 * da2_da1 * da1_dW1\ndLoss_dW2 = dLoss_dOutput * dOutput_dW2\n\nprint(f\"∂Loss/∂w1: {dLoss_dW1:.4f}\")  # ≈ -1.5\nprint(f\"∂Loss/∂w2: {dLoss_dW2:.4f}\")  # ≈ -0.25"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain rule flow"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Loss → output → a₂ → a₁ → w₁\n  ∂L/∂w₁ = ∂L/∂output × ∂output/∂a₂ × ∂a₂/∂a₁ × ∂a₁/∂w₁"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key formulas — Chain rule variations"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Single variable:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"dy/dx = dy/du × du/dx"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-variable (partial derivatives):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"∂z/∂x = ∂z/∂u × ∂u/∂x + ∂z/∂v × ∂v/∂x"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where z = f(u, v) and u, v depend on x"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Extended chain (multiple layers):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"dy/dx = dy/du₁ × du₁/du₂ × du₂/du₃ × ... × duₙ/dx"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mistake"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Correction"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not plugging back inner function"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"f'(g(x)) must have g(x) inside, not just u"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Wrong order"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Always: outer derivative × inner derivative"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Forgetting chain rule"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For composite functions, MUST use chain rule (not just product/sum rule)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Manual computation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use autograd for neural networks"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best practices — Proven approaches"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Use autograd frameworks"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import torch\n\nmodel = NeuralNetwork()\nloss = compute_loss(model(x), y)\n\n# Chain rule automatically applied in backpropagation\nloss.backward()"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Check gradient flow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Monitor for gradient vanishing/explosion\nfor name, param in model.named_parameters():\n    if param.grad is not None:\n        grad_norm = param.grad.norm()\n        print(f\"{name}: gradient norm = {grad_norm:.4f}\")"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Use activation functions with good gradients"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# ReLU avoids vanishing gradient (derivative = 1 for positive inputs)\nactivation = torch.nn.ReLU()"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Chain rule = derivative of composite function"},{"type":"text","text":": dy/dx = dy/du × du/dx"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Outer × inner"},{"type":"text","text":": Derivative of outer function (at inner) × derivative of inner"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Russian nesting dolls"},{"type":"text","text":": Differentiate outer layer, then inner layer, multiply"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Backpropagation = chain rule"},{"type":"text","text":": Neural network training applies chain rule recursively"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Local derivatives"},{"type":"text","text":": Break complex derivative into simple pieces multiplied together"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Extended chain"},{"type":"text","text":": dy/dx = dy/du₁ × du₁/du₂ ×... × duₙ/dx"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Don't forget inner function"},{"type":"text","text":": f'(g(x)) must keep g(x) inside"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Essential for deep learning"},{"type":"text","text":": Enables training 100+ layer networks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use autograd"},{"type":"text","text":": PyTorch/TensorFlow apply chain rule automatically"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Generative AI, the chain rule is the mathematical foundation that makes neural networks trainable: every backpropagation step, every gradient computation, and every weight update relies on the chain rule to decompose the derivative of the loss with respect to millions/billions of parameters into a product of simple local derivatives."}]}]}}
